The artist has his own identity now so it is irrelevant to mention on a song page that he was a former member of band. That information is already there on his wikipedia page.
The artist is known by the mononym Zayn (Stylized as ZAYN). So I changed from capital letters to small letters.

Just added (stylized as '''ZAYN''') in the first line of the page as it is important to know the stage name of the artist which he uses since he went solo. <ref>http://www.billboard.com/artist/7129015/zayn/biography</ref>

Minor change in the birthplace section from United Kingdom to UK as both mean the same and is a common name understood by the viewers.<ref>http://www.historic-uk.com/HistoryUK/HistoryofBritain/The-UK-Great-Britain-Whats-the-Difference/</ref>
Changed the name from [[Zayn Malik]] to [[Zayn Malik|Zayn]] as the singer is now known by the mononym Zayn since he went solo.
Zayn's debut album Mind of Mine was produced by Malay so I added his name in the associated acts <ref>http://ew.com/article/2016/03/25/zayn-malik-mind-of-mine-behind-scenes-malay-ho/</ref>

RCA Records is an American record label owned by Sony Music Entertainment (SME) which is a music company not a record label itself and Zayn is not a Universal Music Group artist<ref>https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_Universal_Music_Group_artists</ref>
Grammar correction from "known predominantly under the mononym" to "known predominantly by the mononym".

Lil Wayne has collaborated with Zayn on the remix of his song "Pillowtalk", So I added him in the Associated Acts section. Source: http://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/pop/6890371/zayn-malik-lil-wayne-pillowtalk-rap-remix.
Zayn is currently signed to RCA Record label which is owned by Sony Music Entertainment not directly with Sony Music and also he is not signed with Universal Music Group so I removed those links.

Just edited the birthplace to align it in one line, corrected the grammar in the first line of the page from "known predominantly under the mononym" to "predominantly by the mononym" and added an associated act with Lil Wayne who collaborated with Zayn
